    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean, i get that people disagree, but it feels like when people call it \"censorship\" they're just trying to dismiss real progress. like, isn't it more accurate to say that what some call \"censorship\" is actually just people being held accountable for being harmful? don't you think the \"censorship\" argument is mostly just a way to avoid social change?",
